        <section ids="feature-verification-test-plan-details" names="feature\ verification\ test\ plan\ details">
            <title>Feature Verification Test Plan details</title>
            <paragraph><reference refuri="https://confluence.amd.com/display/SRDCV/Skin+Temperature+Testing">https://confluence.amd.com/display/SRDCV/Skin+Temperature+Testing</reference></paragraph>
            <paragraph>Step-by-step guide</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Enable EC logs to dump sensor and die data, Steps to run XGMI Temperature Gradient Test</paragraph>
            <block_quote>
                <enumerated_list enumtype="arabic" prefix="" suffix=".">
                    <list_item>
                        <paragraph>Set the temperature chamber to the desired setting (0C or 45C).</paragraph>
                    </list_item>
                    <list_item>
                        <paragraph>Run a stressful graphics app (ex. FurMark) are max settings for 30min to soak ASIC before activating the XGMI link.</paragraph>
                    </list_item>
                    <list_item>
                        <paragraph>Now close the stress graphics app and activate the XGMI link by running a P2P transfer app (ex. Quark)</paragraph>
                    </list_item>
                </enumerated_list>
            </block_quote>
            <paragraph>Steps to run XGMI Ramp Temperature Test</paragraph>
            <block_quote>
                <enumerated_list enumtype="arabic" prefix="" suffix=".">
                    <list_item>
                        <paragraph>Set the temperature chamber to ROOM temperature (25C)</paragraph>
                    </list_item>
                    <list_item>
                        <paragraph>Activate the XGMI link by running a P2P transfer app (ex. Quark).</paragraph>
                    </list_item>
                    <list_item>
                        <paragraph>Change the temperature chamber to the desired setting (0C or 45C) and let the P2P transfer app continue running.</paragraph>
                    </list_item>
                </enumerated_list>
            </block_quote>
            <paragraph>Pass/Fail criteria.</paragraph>
            <block_quote>
                <bullet_list bullet="-">
                    <list_item>
                        <paragraph>There should be no failure during link training while GPUs have temperature Gradient.</paragraph>
                    </list_item>
                    <list_item>
                        <paragraph>There should be no workload failure or corruption.</paragraph>
                    </list_item>
                    <list_item>
                        <paragraph>System is stable with</paragraph>
                        <block_quote>
                            <bullet_list bullet="-">
                                <list_item>
                                    <paragraph>no application hangs.</paragraph>
                                </list_item>
                                <list_item>
                                    <paragraph>no XGMI PCS errors</paragraph>
                                </list_item>
                                <list_item>
                                    <paragraph>No system hang.</paragraph>
                                </list_item>
                                <list_item>
                                    <paragraph>System does not reboot or power off</paragraph>
                                </list_item>
                                <list_item>
                                    <paragraph>System is not slow or unresponsive</paragraph>
                                </list_item>
                            </bullet_list>
                        </block_quote>
                    </list_item>
                </bullet_list>
            </block_quote>
